The image is being cropped because your CSS is probably using:

CSS
object-fit: cover;

cover fills the heart shape but cuts parts of the image.

Tell your agent:

The photos inside the timeline heart frames are being cropped too aggressively.

Please update the image styling so the entire image is visible inside the heart frame.

Requirements:
- Change image fit from `object-fit: cover` to `object-fit: contain`.
- Keep the heart-shaped frame exactly the same.
- Keep the pink glow around the heart.
- Center the image using `object-position: center`.
- Add a blurred version of the same image behind the main image so there are no empty gaps around portrait photos.
- Do not crop faces, shoulders, or important parts of the image.
- Maintain the premium romantic look.

Suggested CSS:

.heart-photo-frame {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.heart-photo-frame::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: inherit;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    filter: blur(20px);
    transform: scale(1.2);
}

.heart-photo-frame img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: contain;
    object-position: center;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
}

Expected result:
The complete image should be visible inside every heart frame while preserving the romantic heart-shaped design and glow effects.

If you want the full face visible with no cropping at all, contain is the correct choice. If you want the heart completely filled, use cover (but some cropping is unavoidable).
